==English==

===Etymology===
[[gut]] (verb) + [[rehab]] (abbr. of [[rehabilitation]])

===Noun===
'''[[gut]] [[rehab]]'''
# A major [[restoration]] project on an old [[house]] or other building, ripping out [[plaster]] [[wall]]s back to the [[stud]]s and [[rafter]]s and replacing them along with some or all of the [[trim]], [[window]]s and [[doors]], [[plumbing]] and [[electrical system]]s, exterior [[siding]], [[roof]], etc.